        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 3:50PM CDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 350 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Springview, moving south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Thomas Creek State Wildlife Management Area and Pine Glen State
Wildlife Refuge.

This includes Highway 183 between mile markers 201 and 203, and
between mile markers 206 and 212.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
